Diagnosis (based on
Cairns, 2001
): Colony bottlebrush, wiry, up to 16 cm in height, with branching sequence 2 / 5 R and a rhizoidal holdfast. Distance between branches is 1.0– 1.5 mm and orthostiche interval between 7.0 and 7.5 mm . First internode from 6 to 8 mm long, with usually one polyp. Presence of 1–3 internodes per branch, usually 2 . Body wall of polyps and tentacular sclerites with rotund rods longitudinally arranged, 0.44–0.65 in length. Coenenchymal scales up to 0.65 mm long. Pinnular and distal tentacle sclerites rectangular to mediallyconstricted scales 0.12–0.20 mm in greater length and 0.0– 0.05 mm in width and with faces sparsely ornamented and edges finely serrate.
